Run dispatches on args[0] to init, todo, reset, link, unlink, list, show, diff, help, or skill. No args, --help, -h, and help all print the help text with exit code 0. Unknown commands return an error message with help text and exit code 1. Missing args for reset/link/unlink/show/diff return a usage message with an example and exit code 1. Reset accepts 1 arg (orphan cleanup) or 2 args (edge resolution). Diff accepts 1 arg (auto-expand) or 2 args (edge-scoped). Before any subcommand dispatches, two uniform checks run on args[1]: (1) the help_flag check, and (2) the unknown_flag_rejection check. Both run for every subcommand including those that take no arguments (init, todo, skill).